\section{Classical Planning}
\label{sec-1}

\uline{\emph{✔}} \textbf{Scalable, Highly-optimized solver} for complex combinatorial problems

\uline{\emph{✔}} Guided by \textbf{domain-independent} heuristics

\textbf{\emph{✘}} \textbf{Requires an explicit encoding} of the real world, written by human

\section{Reinforcement Learning}
\label{sec-2}

Policy function $\pi$(s): S $\rightarrow$ A --- returns action a for state s

Optimal Policy $\pi$$^{\text{*}}$(s)

Goal: Find the best approximation of $\pi^*$

